(1) Larval head elongated and narrowed, with antennae bases brought together, frons narrow and keel-shaped (
Figs 12–13
). In specimens with intensively developed cuticular coloration, cuticle of frons in last larval instar brown (
Fig. 12
), in previous instars colorless (
Fig. 13
